        [
          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "Collaborative Learning",
          "60 nursing students",
          "BSc Program in Nursing",
          "Headset, Positioning Sensor, Video, Evaluation of Team Performance, Post-Activity Survey",
          "None Specified",
          "[Frequency of interaction with environment, Frequency of Communication, Number of times student in a specific communication type]",
          "The problem is framed as tripartite network that for each student and each area of the learning environment characterizes the student relative to the different features. \n\nDifference between groups is assessed using the Mann-Whittney U test ",
          "Stochastic Blockmodel",
          "-",
          "2",
          "Cluster 1 (n=31): Students who exhibited higher satisfaction with the learning activity - as well as containing the largest proportion of high performing students.  \n\nThere 6 patterns that were considered above random - focus on the primary working area and communication focused on exchanging information.\n\nCluster 2 (n=27): Transitioned between more working areas - primary and secondary.\n\n\n",
          "Less movement and more stable patterns of communication behavior contribute to more satisfaction of nursing students.\n\nPotential of multimodal experiments to provide insights on more complex learning tasks.\n\n",
          "Work proposes a tropartite network model to uncover realtionships in collaborative learning. \n\nThe serusts are subsequently clustered and authors find 2 clusters of behavior with distinctions in terms of satisfaction and performance.",
          "Limited context (Healthcare)\n\nSmall sample size."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
